article.headline: Wright St. 64, Detroit 62
article.story: DETROIT -- Kendall Griffin scored 15 points and Wright State withstood a late Detroit rally to win 64-62 on Monday night. Reggie Arceneaux scored 11 points and Cole Darling scored 10 for the Raiders (14-5, 5-1), who moved into a tie with Valparaiso for first place in the Horizon League. Wright State lost to Valparaiso 69-63 on Saturday. Doug Anderson led the Titans (12-8, 4-3) with game highs of 20 points and six rebounds. Nick Minnerath had 12 points for Detroit, and Juwan Howard Jr. and Jason Calliste each scored 10. Ray McCallum had eight points and six assists, and missed a 3-pointer as time ran out. Wright State never trailed, but Detroit tied it at 53 with 5 minutes to play. Darling's three-point play on the Raiders' next possession gave them the lead for good.
